plugin: manual
name: touchpad/basic
_description:
 PURPOSE:
     1. Touchpad verification
 STEPS:
     1. Make sure that touchpad is enabled
     2. Try to move pointer using touchpad
     3. Pointer should move accordingly
 VERIFICATION:
     1. Did touchpad work as expected?

plugin: shell
name: touchpad/detect_horizontal_scroll
depends: touchpad/basic and device.category == "TOUCH"
command: touchpad_scroll_detect 'horizontal'
_description:  Detects that the touchpad supports horizontal scroll using xinput

plugin: shell
name: touchpad/detect_vertical_scroll
depends: touchpad/basic and device.category == "TOUCH"
command: touchpad_scroll_detect 'vertical'
_description:  Detects that the touchpad supports vertical scroll using xinput

plugin: manual
name: touchpad/horizontal
depends: touchpad/basic touchpad/detect_horizontal_scroll
command: touchpad_test right left
_description:
 PURPOSE:
     1. Touchpad verification
 STEPS:
     1. Make sure that touchpad is enabled
     2. Select "Test" when ready and place your cursor within the borders of the displayed test window.
     3. Verify that you can move the the horizontal slider by moving your finger side by side in the lower part of the touchpad
 VERIFICATION:
     1. Did touchpad work as expected?

plugin: manual
name: touchpad/vertical
depends: touchpad/basic touchpad/detect_vertical_scroll
command: touchpad_test up down
_description:
 PURPOSE:
     1. Touchpad verification
 STEPS:
     1. Make sure that touchpad is enabled
     2. Select "Test" when ready and place your cursor within the borders of the displayed test window.
     3. Verify that you can move the the vertical slider by moving your finger side by side in the right part of the touchpad
 VERIFICATION:
     1. Did touchpad work as expected?

